abstract:
A simple mechanical model was recently proposed to explain the universality of stretch at break ({\lambda}_b) as a function of cycle-rank density ({\xi}) in phantom-chain network simulations [J Non-Newtonian Fluid Mech., 349, 105620 (2026)]. Here, that model is reformulated as a series of the bottleneck strand and the surrounding network, yielding {\lambda}_b-1=({\lambda}_bs-1)[1+{
u}_h/(1+c{\xi})]. In this formula, {\lambda}_bsis the stretch at break of the bottleneck strand, {
u}_h is the number of stiff units in series along the rupture path, and c is a geometric constant for the parallel redundancy of the medium. Since c and {
u}_hare difficult to separate over the examined range of {\xi}, c is fixed, and {\lambda}_bs and {
u}_hare treated as fitting parameters. The formula is applied to phantom-chain simulations of networks with various conditions. In all cases, it reasonably captures the data, and the two parameters represent network characteristics.

summary:
最近提出了一个简单的力学模型来解释幻链网络模拟中断裂拉伸 ({\lambda}_b) 作为循环等级密度 ({\xi}) 函数的普遍性 [J Non-Newtonian Fluid Mech., 349, 105620 (2026)]。在这里，该模型被重新表述为一系列瓶颈链和周围网络，产生 {\lambda}_b-1=({\lambda}_bs-1)[1+{
u}_h/(1+c{\xi})]。在此公式中，{\lambda}_b是瓶颈股的断裂伸长率，{
u}_h是沿断裂路径串联的刚性单元的数量，c是介质并联冗余的几何常数。由于 c 和 {
u}_ha 在 {\xi} 的检查范围内难以分离，因此 c 是固定的，而 {\lambda}_bs 和 {
u}_hare 被视为拟合参数。该公式适用于各种条件下网络的幻链模拟。在所有情况下，它都合理地捕获数据，并且这两个参数代表网络特征。
